    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="596"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Greece/5–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Mark F. Ethridge</persName>, at Geneva</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-13">May 13,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>369. For Ethridge. <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> on May 12<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d596fn1">For discussion by the Security Council on that day, see
                            <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">2nd yr., No.
                            39</hi>, p. 825.</note> voted 8–0 with USSR, Poland and Syria
                    abstaining, to invite Balkan Commission’s chief delegates, or alternates, to
                    come to New York in connection with Commission’s report. Consideration of
                    4-point USSR resolution,<note n="2" xml:id="d596fn2">For text, see <hi
                            rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 832.</note> was postponed until May 16.
                    Under this resolution, <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> would limit Subsidiary
                    Group to carrying out and reporting on each separate Commission-ordered
                    investigation of facts. Group’s headquarters would be Athens and its functions
                    would be limited to those assigned by Commission. It would cease activity with
                    termination of Commission, and Commission would redefine Group’s terms of
                    reference in accord with this proposed <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                    resolution.</p>
                <p>Verbatim <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> minutes follow by pouch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
